cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses neural network techniques such as batch normalization and ReLU, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also includes experiments on image classification tasks, which suggests a possible fit for cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the proposed generalized hamming network has potential applications in control systems, which could place the paper in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
